==Korean==
===Verb===
'''나다''' (na-da)
# To be [[born]], cf. Latin [[nasci]]  
# To [[appear]], [[arise]], [[occur]], [[take place]]
# To [[break out]], [[come out]], [[turn out]]
# To [[grow]], [[spread]] 

====Derived terms====
* [[깨다|깨어]]나다 (kkaeEo-) To become [[awake]]n, [[enlighten]]ed
* [[나오다]] (nao-da) To [[come out]], literally "to out come"
* [[나타나다]] (nata-) To [[appear]]
* [[돋다|돋아]]나다 (dodA-) To [[sprout]], [[bud]] out 
* [[붇다|불어]]나다 (burEo-) To [[grow]] larger
* [[솟다|솟아]]나다 (sosA-) To come to [[rise]]
* [[살다|살아]]나다 (sarA-) To get [[alive]]
* [[일다|일어]]나다 (irEo-) To [[break out]], [[arise]] 
* [[자라다|자라]]나다 (jara-) To [[grow]] larger
* [[태어나다]] (taeEo-) To be [[born]]

====Related terms====

====See also====
* [[낳다]] (nah-da, nat-ta) To [[lay]] (egg), [[give birth]], cf. Latin [[nasci]] "to be born"

